value.0: "How are you, my friend? Are you ready to send me to my final rest?"
Kaidala, the nymph druid, rises over her corpse, smiling, until she begins to listen to an inaudible voice. The voice upsets her and she turns her large, watery eyes towards you.
"Death is not so terrible, <FirstName>. Finally I can go and be happy, as I never could be in life. You know well how hard these years have been to me, so I do hope you will let me go."
"The others all want to live, so I make your choice easier. Take two of them and leave me be."
"What was there in life for me that was so great? I am happy to finally be rid of that burden."
"I do not understand what you are talking about. Truly, I tell you it is not so bad here. Once you let me go, I shall move on to a nicer place, of that I am confident."
"It cannot see Blackest Death, but soon it shall feel our teeth and our claws."
"What are you talking about, <FirstName>? It is only you and I and the voice that told me to wait for your choice."
"I am one of the soul harvesters. I am that which waits and steals. There is a fate that waits for those who strive to end their own lives. Those who despise themselves."
"There is much sustenance to be found in the pain and agony of a soul such as this! I cannot touch you, nor can you touch me. I am Blackest Death for those who are dead."
"I shall await your decision."
"There is something wrong with you, <FirstName>, I can sense your distress. Who do you speak to? Tell me, is there anything I can do to ease your mind?"
"Indeed, it is what waits for all who cannot bear to live. I shall await your decision."
"It has been done before, this is true; but long and hard is that road. I think you shall not succeed. I shall await your decision."
"There is something wrong with you, <FirstName>, I can sense your distress. Who do you speak to? Tell me, is there anything I can do to ease your mind?"
"I shall await your decision."
"No! You cannot choose me! Let the others live, <FirstName>. I am happy in death."
"There should be no need. You can leave me here and rest easy with your decision."
"Do not be long, lifeholder. I grow impatient."
"I am ready to hear it. May I rest from my journey now, or do you still require my assistance?"
"I don't see what choice there is to make, but take all the time you need. I am content here."

LinkComment.value: The soul harvester and Kaidala fade away, with Kaidala's death sceam.

value.0: Kaidala's soul lets out a deafening screech as the soul harvester drags it off into eternal torture.
She smiles and says, "Thank you." Then suddenly she turns and sees the soul harvester waiting for her. "Noooooooooo!"
She heaves a heavy sigh. "So be it. I shall do my best."
"I will do my best. It is the least I can do for you."
"Will you go and speak to the others now? Or have you made your choice?"
"I know he is a good man, but Calibast's fiery countenance is too much for me. It is harder for me to be near him. I would not condemn him to death for it though."
"Indeed, I view all of our companions as far more worthy than I."
"I owe them nothing less. They have all helped me in the past. I would do anything to help them, or you."
"Of course I would... if that is necessary. He has always been kind to me, and it is in my mind alone that he would pose a danger to me. Fires took my home, and he is a creature of fire."
"His passions run hot, for drinking, wenching, and fighting. It bothers me some, but... he is a good man, I believe."
"All of his passions burn hot. I have even thought that his fascination with you maybe burned hotter than any... but I could be wrong. It is not my place to say such things."

"I am a druid, and can heal you, or wield the powers of nature to assist you. I do not fear death, so I am not afraid to enter battle either. I prefer to use natural weapons, such as a club or quarterstaff."
"If I had my former powers back... then I would be formidable indeed. But that is in the past. The destruction of my home ruined me, and stole my natural gifts."
"The terror of the night when my forest was put to the torch by superstitious fools is burnt into my mind for eternity."
"The flames roared and devoured all of my creatures. All of my sisters, the dryads. Even me. The flames licked at my face and my hair. The flesh on my body was scorched black when you found me."

"Oh, <FirstName>, the pain in my body is gone, but my mind and my soul... they burn, even now they still burn." Tears flow down her cheeks, the scars on the one side are still red and sore, despite the passage of time.
"No, it is in the past, the present and the future. Every time I see my reflection, every time I close my eyes to sleep, every time I run a hand over my ravaged face, it is there to haunt me."
"Maybe to you it is just a moment in history; to me it is the only moment... the only one that matters."
"We... we tried, but the earth where my forest stood, it is scarred. The people who burned it... they make certain that nothing grows on it. Even the smallest shoot is quickly pulled or burned."
"There is no future for me. Not in this life. Even you must see that."
She stares at you with hollow eyes. "Go away, <FirstName>. I wish to be free of your company. Free of this wretched existence. Choose someone else to torment."
She smiles hesitantly at you, for the first time in many months. "You are too optimistic for this world, <FirstName>. You shame me. I guess sometimes that is a good thing."
"What else would you like to discuss?"
"It... it is understandable. If only time could hold still for a while, that I could catch my breath. Maybe then the pain would be eased."
"But you have a choice to make. What more do you need from me?"
"I have noticed you speaking to something, but whatever you think you see, it is not real, <FirstName>. Put it from your mind. Obviously your own death has scattered your wits."
"You have been a... friend... of sorts. Perhaps you were my only friend, but I do not think that is enough for me to hold onto life. Have pity and let me go!"
"Please, <FirstName>, though I have grown fond of you, there has never been anything more than friendship between us. Perhaps if we had more time together..."
"But no... no one could ever love a scarred and maimed creature such as myself. Have pity on me, <FirstName>. Let me go."
Kaidala smiles sadly at you. "That is for the best, as I have said all along."
"Still, if my healing arts are needed, then I shall do my best to assist you."
"I know we have, but all good things must come to an end. You should let me go; but if you choose otherwise, then I promise you my best."
Kaidala's eyes mist over. "If... if it means so much to you, then I will join you. But I think it is not fair to our other companions."

"I shall devote my healing powers, and as many of the powers of nature still in my command to your service. You do hold a special place in my heart, <FirstName>, perhaps we shall see where it leads us."
"You don't want another chance at life?"
"Death will not be pleasant for you."
"What is the creature that stands behind you?"
"I shall destroy you first!"
"Why do you wait for her?"
"Tell me what you are, foul creature!"
"What do I care? If I don't choose her, you can have her."
"This is the price she must pay then."
"Even if you take her, I shall find a way to free her from you, someday!"
"You cannot touch her if I choose to bring her back!"
"I need to speak to the others before I decide."
"I have made a choice."
"I've made a mistake. I need a little more time before I choose."
"Enjoy your time in the underworld; you'll not be leaving it soon!"
"I cannot choose you, Kaidala."

"I would like you to return and assist me."

value.0: "I have a few questions for you."
"That is all my questions."
"Who would you say I should not choose?"
"I have other questions."
"That is an admirable sentiment."
"Would you work with Calibast if I chose both of you?"
"What skills do you have, exactly?"
"Why do you long to die?"
"You are of little use to me in this condition."
"You need to get over this. It's in the past."
"Why couldn't you be healed?"
"You disgust me with your pathetic sniveling."
"I suppose you are right."
"I shall never give up!"
"We will find a way to heal you."
"I am sorry to bring back those memories."
"There is something waiting to torture your soul."
"Then I guess you shall die."
"How can you know what feelings I have for you, if you die?"
"We have had some good times together, Kaidala."
"Is our friendship not enough to make you want to live?"
